e></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533975\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 18, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xyc1665702738616.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xyc1665702738616.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xyc1665702738616.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xyc1665702738616\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Start or Stop the Uniface Router on iSeries\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You start the Uniface Router by starting the subsystem (if you chose to create a\n      subsystem during installation), or by calling <span class=\"ph filepath\">STARTUP</span>.</p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"xyc1665702738616__topic_d31127e1_d31128e1_d31129e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xyc1665702738616__p_d31133e1_d31134e1_d31135e1\">If you created a subsystem during installation, there will be a subsystem description in your installation library. The names of library and subsystem normally have the form <code class=\"ph codeph\">UNIF<var class=\"keyword varname\">VersionNumber</var>\n</code>, for example, <code class=\"ph codeph\">UNIF10302</code>, but you may have chosen a different name.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section p\" id=\"xyc1665702738616__section_w1373ab1b5b3_w1374ab1b5_w1375ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xyc1665702738616__p_d31136e1_d31137e1_d31138e1\">To start the Uniface Router:</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section ul\" id=\"xyc1665702738616__section_w1376ab1b5b5_w1377ab1b5_w1378ab1\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xyc1665702738616__li_d15896e1_d15897e1_d15898e1\">Using the subsystem, enter the following command:\n <p class=\"p\" id=\"xyc1665702738616__p_d31139e1_d31140e1_d31141e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">STRSBS</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">LibraryName</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">/</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">SubsystemName</var>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xyc1665702738616__p_d31142e1_d31143e1_d31144e1\">For example, assuming the library is <code class=\"ph codeph\">UNIFxxxx</code> and the subsystem name is also <code class=\"ph codeph\">UNIFxxxx</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">STRSBS UNIFxxxx/UNIFxxxx</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xyc1665702738616__p_d31145e1_d31146e1_d31147e1\">This starts the subsystem, which has an autostart job that runs the <span class=\"ph filepath\">STARTUP</span>program. <span class=\"ph filepath\">STARTUP</span>, in its turn, starts the <span class=\"ph filepath\">UROUTER</span> using the TCP port number and user profile that you specified during installation.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xyc1665702738616__li_d15899e1_d15900e1_d15901e1\">If no subsystem was created, enter the following command:\n <p class=\"p\" id=\"xyc1665702738616__p_d31148e1_d31149e1_d31150e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">CALL</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">LibraryName</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">/STARTUP</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xyc1665702738616__p_d31151e1_d31152e1_d31153e1\">For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">CALL UNIFxxxx/STARTUP</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section p\" id=\"xyc1665702738616__section_w1379ab1b5b7_w1380ab1b5_w1381ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xyc1665702738616__p_d31154e1_d31155e1_d31156e1\">To stop the Uniface Router:</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section ul\" id=\"xyc1665702738616__section_w1382ab1b5b9_w1383ab1b5_w1384ab1\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xyc1665702738616__li_d15902e1_d15903e1_d15904e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xyc1665702738616__p_d31157e1_d31158e1_d31159e1\">If you have created a subsystem, enter the following command:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">ENDSBS (UNIFxxxx) OPTION(*IMMED)</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xyc1665702738616__li_d15905e1_d15906e1_d15907e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xyc1665702738616__p_d31160e1_d31161e1_d31162e1\">If you did not create a subsystem, enter the following command (assuming that UROUTER is listening to port 13001):</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">CHGCURLIB UNIFxxxx\nCALL PGM(UROUTER) PARM('TCP:+13001' '/shut')</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"xyc1665702738616__note_w1385ab1b5b9b1b3b5_w1386ab1b5b9b1b3_w1387ab1b5b9b1_w1388ab1b5b9_w1389ab1b5_w1390ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> You can also stop the UROUTER in this way if you have created a subsystem for it, but that will leave the subsystem running. In this case, restarting the UROUTER later on cannot be done by starting the subsystem, but must be done by running STARTUP.</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/exm1665702529212.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface Router</a><p>The Uniface Router is a multi-threaded process (urouter) responsible for interprocess communication in Uniface applications. It listens for requests from Uniface client applications and routes them to the appropriate Uniface Server, and it passes messages between various Uniface applications.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533975\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533975\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Start or Stop the Uniface Router on iSeries Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 18, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Start or Stop the Uniface Router on iSeries You start the Uniface Router by starting the subsystem (if you chose to create a subsystem during installation), or by calling STARTUP . If you created a subsystem during installation, there will be a subsystem description in your installation library. The names of library and subsystem normally have the form UNIF VersionNumber , for example, UNIF10302 , but you may have chosen a different name. To start the Uniface Router: Using the subsystem, enter the following command: STRSBS LibraryName / SubsystemName For example, assuming the library is UNIFxxxx and the subsystem name is also UNIFxxxx : STRSBS UNIFxxxx/UNIFxxxx Copy This starts the subsystem, which has an autostart job that runs the STARTUP program. STARTUP , in its turn, starts the UROUTER using the TCP port number and user profile that you specified during installation. If no subsystem was created, enter the following command: CALL LibraryName /STARTUP For example: CALL UNIFxxxx/STARTUP Copy To stop the Uniface Router: If you have created a subsystem, enter the following command: ENDSBS (UNIFxxxx) OPTION(*IMMED) Copy If you did not create a subsystem, enter the following command (assuming that UROUTER is listening to port 13001): CHGCURLIB UNIFxxxx CALL PGM(UROUTER) PARM('TCP:+13001' '/shut') Copy Note: You can also stop the UROUTER in this way if you have created a subsystem for it, but that will leave the subsystem running. In this case, restarting the UROUTER later on cannot be done by starting the subsystem, but must be done by running STARTUP. Related Links Uniface Router The Uniface Router is a multi-threaded process (urouter) responsible for interprocess communication in Uniface applications. It listens for requests from Uniface client applications and routes them to the appropriate Uniface Server, and it passes messages between various Uniface applications. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}